message: The Geisters spend hours working with victims of trafficking. It's a cause that at one time, they didn't even know they were passionate about. "It's a wake up call because I would have never imagined that such a thing would be. I would never imagine that humanity is so cruel," Linda said.

data.description: Hunters across the country are coming to South Dakota for pheasant season. But that big event also fuels sex trafficking right in our own backyard.
data.title: Husband And Wife Fight Against Human Trafficking
